## 📘 User Guide

This guide will help you quickly integrate and use the reusable table component in your Angular application.

---

### 🔹 Step 1: Install the Package

```bash
npm install @tasktrack/reusable-table
```

---

### 🔹 Step 2: Import the Module

Add the module to your Angular app:

```ts
import { ReusableTableModule } from '@tasktrack/reusable-table';

@NgModule({
  imports: [ReusableTableModule]
})
export class AppModule {}
```

---

### 🔹 Step 3: Define Table Columns

Columns control what is displayed in the table.

```ts
columns = [
  { key: 'id', label: 'ID' },
  { key: 'name', label: 'Name' },
  { key: 'email', label: 'Email' }
];
```

---

### 🔹 Step 4: Provide Table Data

Pass an array of objects as table data.

```ts
data = [
  { id: 1, name: 'John Doe', email: 'john@example.com' },
  { id: 2, name: 'Jane Doe', email: 'jane@example.com' }
];
```

---

### 🔹 Step 5: Use the Component

```html
<app-reusable-table
  [columns]="columns"
  [data]="data"
  (action)="handleAction($event)">
</app-reusable-table>
```

---

### 🔹 Step 6: Handle Actions

The table emits events when user interacts with action buttons.

```ts
handleAction(event: any) {
  console.log(event);

  // Example:
  // event.type => 'edit' | 'delete' | 'view'
  // event.row => selected row data
}
```

---

### 🔹 Inputs

| Input   | Type  | Description           |
| ------- | ----- | --------------------- |
| columns | Array | Defines table columns |
| data    | Array | Data to be displayed  |

---

### 🔹 Outputs

| Output | Description                            |
| ------ | -------------------------------------- |
| action | Emits when an action button is clicked |

---

### 🔹 Tips

* You can dynamically update columns and data
* Works seamlessly with Angular Material themes
* Extendable for custom actions and features

---

### 🔹 Common Issues

* Make sure Angular Material is installed
* Ensure Angular version matches library version (Angular 18+)
* Import the module correctly

---

### 🔹 Best Practice

* Keep data structure consistent with column keys
* Handle actions in a centralized method
* Use clean UI for better readability
